 bake in hot\noven <4OO degrees) 1 hour or\nuntil done. Marinate oysters in\nFrench dressing 30 minutes.\nDrain. Cut potatoes lengthwise\nin halves and scoop out inside.\nMash, add butter and hot nulk,\nand season with salt and pepper.\nBeat until light and fluffy.\nPile mixture into potato shells,\nmaking a hollow in center of\neach half. Arrange oysters in\nhollows in potatoes. Top with\nbuttered crumbs, sprinkle with\npaprika, and return to oven lo\nminutes, or untd crumbs ate\nbrowned. Serves 8.\nBEDTIME DOLL\nNOWS THE time to start\nthinking of what in make for\nthe little one in your house\nfor Christmas. She'd love this\nsleepy doll in cunning pajamas.\nUse yarn for the hair; your\nlot will love it if it matches\nher own! Pattern 503 has di\nrections for doll and pajamas.\nSend 15 cents in coins for\nevery Laura Wheeler pattern.\nWrite name and address plainly.\nOnly 15 rents more brings\nyou our newest needlecraft\ncatalog .the 104 b edition\n112 illustrations of de\nsigns for crochet, knitting,\nquilts, embroidery, toys, handi\ncraft a frep pattern for\ncuddle toys printed right in the\ncatalog.\nSend your order to the Laura\nWheeler Pattern Department,\nThe Detroit Times. Detroit 31,\nMich.\nTitc 'Zf<su%\nFREE\ncoupon\nEvery home in Detroit\nwill get one!\nworth\nJOe on tho\npurchase of any tiio\nr?e*4et'd\nVELVET\nCAKE FIOUR\no% 'tVodUC*\nRobin Hood\nFLOUR\nMilled here in Detroit\u2014\nbetter baking gooron\nteed or your money\nbock plut 10%!\nJ\n1\n'iM' F f\nlOT w f\n\nKATHERINE RATTO\nWill S|\u00bbertk to Fashion (iroiip\nMERCHANDISE EXPERT\nKatherine Ratto will be guest\nspeaker w hen tlie 1* ashion\nGroup of Detroit opens its see*\nond season with a Junrheon\nmeeting Friday, 12:15, Hotel\nStatlcr.\nPossessing a background in\nfashion work ihat includes buy\ning. selling, advertising, promo\ntion. display and personnel\nwork, Mrs. Raito heads the\nmerchandising service depart\nment of the Mart. Chicago's\n\u00a9gigantic market building de\nvoted io app